@startuml
title Athena JS CLI behavior before help + error normalization

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam Rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #FFE5CC
  BorderColor #B45F06
}
skinparam ArrowColor #7A7A7A

actor "Developer" as Dev

rectangle "parseCommand(argv)" as Parse #FCE5CD
rectangle "runSchemaGenerator(...)" as Run #FFF2CC
rectangle "bin catch console.error(err)" as BinCatch #F8CECC
rectangle "Terminal output" as Output #F4CCCC

Dev --> Parse : athena-js generate --help
Parse --> Output : throws Unknown option "--help"

Dev --> Parse : athena-js generate --config ...
Parse --> Run : command accepted
Run --> BinCatch : postgres 3D000 bubbles up
BinCatch --> Output : raw stack + pg internals

note right of Output
Two UX gaps:
1) subcommand help flag is rejected.
2) missing database errors are verbose and noisy.
end note

@enduml
